The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, July 19, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, July 18: Two-wheeler sales rose 10.4 per cent in April-June to 13.6 lakh units from 12.3 a year ago, data compiled by the Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers (SIAM) showed. Motorcycle and step-thru sales, which constituted 78.5 per cent of the total two-wheeler sales, rose 10.2 per cent at 1.07 lakh units. Scooter and scooterettee sales increased 11.8 per cent at 2.18 lakh units, while moped sales jumped 8.61 per cent at 74,980 units.																								 New Delhi, July 18: Reliance Industries chairman Mukesh Ambani has petitioned petroleum minister Mani Shankar Aiyar to secure the right to lay a pipeline for transporting gas from its field in the Bay of Bengal to the customers in the western region.																								 Calcutta, July 18: Allahabad Bank has decided to revive its idle subsidiary, Allbank Financial Services. The bank has appointed Ernst and Young to suggest ways to implement business process engineering to improve the banks services and increase total business to over Rs 61,000 crore in 2004-05.
